WEBVTT

00:04.833 --> 00:06.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.033 --> 00:07.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.466 --> 00:09.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
Justice under fire.

00:09.566 --> 00:14.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the six-month anniversary
of his taking office, President
Trump goes public with his

00:16.533 --> 00:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regret over his choice for
attorney general, while blasting
the FBI and the special counsel

00:21.133 --> 00:23.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
investigating Russia.

00:23.233 --> 00:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Then: stepping back in Syria.

00:26.300 --> 00:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump ends a covert
operation arming rebel fighters,
a move that eases pressure

00:32.466 --> 00:35.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
on both Presidents
Assad and Putin.

00:35.400 --> 00:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Plus: Making Sense of fears
over the rise of artificial
intelligence, and how to curb

00:41.300 --> 00:43.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the future power of computers.

00:43.300 --> 00:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICK BOSTROM, Oxford University:
How could you then ensure
that you could control what

00:46.800 --> 00:51.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
those machines do, that they
were beneficial, that they were
aligned with human intentions?

00:51.633 --> 00:56.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:00.500 --> 01:03.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:03.366 --> 01:08.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President
Trump sounding off again.

01:11.466 --> 01:16.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This time, as he observes
the first half-year
mark of his presidency,
he's vented some very

01:18.366 --> 01:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
public criticism of his attorney
general and of other top
Justice Department officials,

01:22.933 --> 01:24.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
past and present.

01:24.300 --> 01:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang begins our coverage.

01:26.233 --> 01:28.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS, U.S. Attorney
General: Good morning.

01:28.766 --> 01:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Attorney General
Jeff Sessions made it clear
today he's not going anywhere

01:33.166 --> 01:34.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for now.

01:34.166 --> 01:35.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: We love this job.

01:35.566 --> 01:37.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We love this department.

01:37.100 --> 01:40.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I plan to continue to do so,
as long as that is appropriate.

01:40.700 --> 01:45.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: That came after
President Trump's sharp rebuke
of Sessions in a New York Times

01:45.400 --> 01:49.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
interview for disqualifying
himself from the
Russia investigation.

01:49.066 --> 01:52.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: How do you take
a job, and then recuse yourself?

01:52.233 --> 01:53.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If he would have recused
himself before the job, I would
have said, thanks, Jeff, but

01:53.500 --> 01:58.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I can't -- you know, I'm
not going to take you.

01:59.800 --> 02:02.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's extremely unfair,
and that's a mild
word, to the president.

02:02.933 --> 02:07.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Trump also said
Sessions gave some bad answers
in his Senate confirmation

02:09.900 --> 02:12.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hearing when he failed
to disclose meetings with
the Russian ambassador.

02:12.833 --> 02:17.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While the White House said
the president still has
confidence in Sessions,
Mr. Trump's comments

02:17.733 --> 02:21.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mark a public break from one
of his earliest supporters.

02:21.633 --> 02:26.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It also suggests that
Mr. Trump's anger with
Sessions is still fresh
more than four months

02:27.733 --> 02:30.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
after the attorney
general recused himself.

02:30.366 --> 02:35.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the 50-minute interview, Mr.
Trump leveled a new allegation
about why fired FBI Director

02:37.766 --> 02:41.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
James Comey told him
about the uncorroborated
contents of a salacious
dossier before Inauguration

02:43.600 --> 02:48.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Day: "In my opinion, he
shared it so that I would
think he had it out there."

02:49.266 --> 02:50.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He was asked, "As leverage?"

02:50.533 --> 02:53.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
"Yes, I think so,
in retrospect."

02:53.400 --> 02:58.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president also
appeared to warn special
counsel Robert Mueller to
limit his investigation.

03:00.466 --> 03:01.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION: Mueller was looking
at your finances, your family's
finances unrelated to Russia.

03:01.266 --> 03:02.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Is that a red line?

03:02.766 --> 03:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: Well, that be a breach
of what his actual charge is?

03:06.866 --> 03:09.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I would say yes.

03:09.733 --> 03:11.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I would say yes.

03:11.233 --> 03:12.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Could Mueller's
investigation go there?

03:12.800 --> 03:15.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Greg Farrell is a Bloomberg
News investigative reporter.

03:15.566 --> 03:17.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GREG FARRELL, Bloomberg News:
That's what this is all about.

03:17.533 --> 03:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have to look into Trump's
own finances and see if there's
been any unusual benefit

03:24.566 --> 03:27.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
beyond the purchase of
apartments, if there's
anything unusual about all
the business transactions

03:27.266 --> 03:31.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that have taken place
over many years between
Russian nationals and him.

03:31.000 --> 03:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Although the White
House said the president
doesn't intend to fire Mueller,

03:35.233 --> 03:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his comments raised red flags
for some Senate Judiciary
Committee Democrats.

03:39.933 --> 03:41.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:41.866 --> 03:45.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD BLUMENTHAL (D),
Connecticut: What we're watching
is an obstruction of justice

03:45.800 --> 03:50.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
case unfolding in real
time right before our
eyes, the president of
the United States trying

03:50.666 --> 03:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to set limits on a
legitimate investigation.

03:53.866 --> 03:55.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:55.900 --> 03:58.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY KLOBUCHAR (D), Minnesota:
Mueller has the right to
investigate this, and he was

03:58.066 --> 04:02.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
given that authority by
the Justice Department,
and he reports to the
Justice Department and

04:03.966 --> 04:05.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
not to the president
of the United States.

04:05.633 --> 04:08.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Committee
Chairman Chuck Grassley
said he wasn't worried.

04:08.800 --> 04:10.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:10.900 --> 04:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLES GRASSLEY (R), Iowa:
As I know Mueller or 13 years
or how many years he was head

04:15.933 --> 04:18.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the FBI, he's
going to do his job.

04:18.966 --> 04:21.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's all that matters.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Grassley said Donald
Trump Jr. and former Trump
campaign chairman Paul Manafort

04:25.066 --> 04:30.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have not yet responded to his
request that they testify next
week and that he will subpoena

04:31.066 --> 04:32.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
them if necessary.

04:32.766 --> 04:34.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm John Yang.

04:34.933 --> 04:39.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will explore
some of the implications of
the president's comments after

04:39.700 --> 04:41.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the news summary.

04:41.733 --> 04:46.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In the day's other news:
Russia's official RIA
news agency reported
the U.S. and Russia

04:47.466 --> 04:51.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are talking about creating a
cyber-security working group.

04:51.166 --> 04:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump had raised a
similar idea during the G20
summit, but backed off under

04:55.733 --> 04:57.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
heavy criticism.

04:57.766 --> 05:02.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This latest report comes amid
multiple U.S. investigations
of Russian meddling in the

05:02.800 --> 05:04.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
2016 election.

05:04.833 --> 05:09.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Congressional Budget Office
says that a revised Senate
Republican health care bill

05:11.133 --> 05:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
leaves as many people uninsured
as a previous version.

05:14.400 --> 05:19.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The CBO reported today
that, under the bill,
another 22 million Americans
would lose coverage

05:20.400 --> 05:22.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by 2026.

05:22.366 --> 05:27.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The measure would also reduce
federal deficits by $420
billion over the coming decade.

05:28.866 --> 05:33.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So far, GOP leaders still lack
the votes to debate the bill.

05:33.633 --> 05:38.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The health of Senator
John McCain dominated this
day at the U.S. Capitol.

05:38.600 --> 05:43.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Arizona Republican has been
diagnosed with brain cancer,
and doctors removed a tumor,

05:44.766 --> 05:47.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
but McCain may need
additional treatment.

05:47.466 --> 05:52.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The news stunned lawmakers from
both parties, who said they're
hoping for the best for their

05:53.200 --> 05:53.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
longtime colleague.

05:53.966 --> 05:55.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:55.366 --> 05:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PATRICK LEAHY (D), Vermont:
He's a good friend.

05:56.300 --> 05:57.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We agree and we disagree.

05:57.766 --> 05:59.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he's one of the oldest
-- he keeps his word.

05:59.300 --> 06:03.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I know we will be praying
for him at mass this weekend.

06:08.400 --> 06:09.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:09.833 --> 06:11.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: He may outlive us all.

06:11.300 --> 06:13.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know what -- God only
knows how this thing ends.

06:13.466 --> 06:18.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I just ask God for one thing,
that he has a voice and he can
use it as long as possible.

06:20.433 --> 06:23.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: McCain is 80,
having survived seven years in
a North Vietnamese prison during

06:25.033 --> 06:26.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Vietnam War.

06:26.966 --> 06:31.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was a Republican presidential
nominee in 2008 and is
serving his sixth term in the

06:31.833 --> 06:33.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Senate.

06:33.566 --> 06:36.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
